    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-07-01T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-07-01T05:00:00-05:00" n="179"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d179">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">462.00R296/4230: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Garrett</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-07-01T11:00:00+01:00"
                            >July 1, 1931—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 1:03 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>116. My 109, June 25, 3 p.m.<note n="21" xml:id="d179fn21">Not printed.</note>
                    Following communiqué published this morning: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“In expectation of an early definite agreement as a result of present
                            negotiations among all the interested governments, the Italian
                            Government as a consequence of its attitude of full and cordial
                            adherence to President Hoover’s proposal, has taken preliminary measures
                            to put the American Plan into effect. For this purpose the Minister for
                            Foreign Affairs in accord with the Minister of Finance has informed the
                            Governments of its debtor States that the Italian Government does not
                            intend to claim the payments falling due to it on July 1 under the Young
                            Plan and the Hague Agreements.</p>
                        <p>It has simultaneously informed the Governments of creditor States that
                            the Royal Government is holding in reserve pending a decision the
                            payments which Italy is due to pay on the same date”.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>Minister for Foreign Affairs informs me that payments due to the creditor States
                    will be deposited in a suspense account with the Bank of International
                    Settlements.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Garrett</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
